# Frontend

- Server Components by default; add "use client" only for interactivity
  (forms, state, effects, event handlers) at the lowest leaf possible.
- Build UI from the vendored component set: shadcn/ui (on Base UI, not Radix)
  for every foundational control; MagicUI for micro-interactions; Aceternity
  for visual identity moments; Efferd for page-level blocks. They live in
  `src/components/{ui,magic,aceternity,blocks}` — edit locally, never add a
  runtime dependency on their upstream packages.
- Tailwind v4: design tokens and keyframes live in `@theme` inside
  `globals.css`. There is no `tailwind.config.ts` — do not create one. Use v4
  class spellings (e.g. `bg-linear-to-br`).
- Every animated component consumes the global `useReducedMotion` gate;
  `prefers-reduced-motion` must remove all nonessential motion with zero
  content loss. Motion via `motion/react` behind the root `LazyMotion`
  provider; animate on viewport entry, never on mount.
- State: Zustand is scoped to the profile + assessment session store
  (`src/store/useAssessmentStore.ts`, localStorage-persisted). Server data is
  never mirrored into client state.
- Keep components small, composable, and typed; props via explicit interfaces,
  no any.
- Validate form input on the client with the same zod schema used server-side.
- Accessibility: semantic elements, labeled inputs, aria-invalid on errors,
  logical focus order, visible focus ring, contrast in light and dark themes.
  The full journey must be keyboard-completable.
- Responsive: mobile-first for budget Android (360 px up); primary actions in
  the thumb zone; verify sm, md, lg breakpoints.
- Show loading, empty, and error states for every async view.
- Never place secrets in client code; only NEXT_PUBLIC_* values are available.
